138// computes cubic spline coefficients for a function: (xi=i, yi=f[i]), i=0..n
139template<typename _Tp> static void splineBuild(const _Tp* f, int n, _Tp* tab)
140{
141 _Tp cn = 0;
142 int i;
143 tab[0] = tab[1] = (_Tp)0;
144
145 for(i = 1; i < n-1; i++)
146 {
147 _Tp t = 3*(f[i+1] - 2*f[i] + f[i-1]);
148 _Tp l = 1/(4 - tab[(i-1)*4]);
149 tab[i*4] = l; tab[i*4+1] = (t - tab[(i-1)*4+1])*l;
150 }
151
152 for(i = n-1; i >= 0; i--)
153 {
154 _Tp c = tab[i*4+1] - tab[i*4]*cn;
155 _Tp b = f[i+1] - f[i] - (cn + c*2)*(_Tp)0.3333333333333333;
156 _Tp d = (cn - c)*(_Tp)0.3333333333333333;
157 tab[i*4] = f[i]; tab[i*4+1] = b;
158 tab[i*4+2] = c; tab[i*4+3] = d;
159 cn = c;
160 }
161}
162
163// interpolates value of a function at x, 0 <= x <= n using a cubic spline.
164template<typename _Tp> static inline _Tp splineInterpolate(_Tp x, const _Tp* tab, int n)
165{
166 // don't touch this function without urgent need - some versions of gcc fail to inline it correctly
167 int ix = std::min(std::max(int(x), 0), n-1);
168 x -= ix;
169 tab += ix*4;
170 return ((tab[3]*x + tab[2])*x + tab[1])*x + tab[0];
171}

174template<typename _Tp> struct ColorChannel
175{
176 typedef float worktype_f;
177 static _Tp max() { return std::numeric_limits<_Tp>::max(); }
178 static _Tp half() { return (_Tp)(max()/2 + 1); }
179};
180
181template<> struct ColorChannel<float>
182{
183 typedef float worktype_f;
184 static float max() { return 1.f; }
185 static float half() { return 0.5f; }
186};

198template <typename Cvt>
199class CvtColorLoop_Invoker : public ParallelLoopBody
200{
201 typedef typename Cvt::channel_type _Tp;
202public:
203
204 CvtColorLoop_Invoker(const Mat& _src, Mat& _dst, const Cvt& _cvt) :
205 ParallelLoopBody(), src(_src), dst(_dst), cvt(_cvt)
206 {
207 }
208
209 virtual void operator()(const Range& range) const
210 {
211 const uchar* yS = src.ptr<uchar>(range.start);
212 uchar* yD = dst.ptr<uchar>(range.start);
213
214 for( int i = range.start; i < range.end; ++i, yS += src.step, yD += dst.step )
215 cvt((const _Tp*)yS, (_Tp*)yD, src.cols);
216 }
217
218private:
219 const Mat& src;
220 Mat& dst;
221 const Cvt& cvt;
222
223 const CvtColorLoop_Invoker& operator= (const CvtColorLoop_Invoker&);
224};
225
226template <typename Cvt>
227void CvtColorLoop(const Mat& src, Mat& dst, const Cvt& cvt)
228{
229 parallel_for_(Range(0, src.rows), CvtColorLoop_Invoker<Cvt>(src, dst, cvt), src.total()/(double)(1<<16) );
230}

234typedef IppStatus (CV_STDCALL* ippiGeneralFunc)(const void *, int, void *, int, IppiSize);

237template <typename Cvt>
238class CvtColorIPPLoop_Invoker : public ParallelLoopBody
239{
240public:
241
242 CvtColorIPPLoop_Invoker(const Mat& _src, Mat& _dst, const Cvt& _cvt, bool *_ok) :
243 ParallelLoopBody(), src(_src), dst(_dst), cvt(_cvt), ok(_ok)
244 {
245 *ok = true;
246 }
247
248 virtual void operator()(const Range& range) const
249 {
250 const void *yS = src.ptr<uchar>(range.start);
251 void *yD = dst.ptr<uchar>(range.start);
252 if( !cvt(yS, (int)src.step[0], yD, (int)dst.step[0], src.cols, range.end - range.start) )
253 *ok = false;
254 }
255
256private:
257 const Mat& src;
258 Mat& dst;
259 const Cvt& cvt;
260 bool *ok;
261
262 const CvtColorIPPLoop_Invoker& operator= (const CvtColorIPPLoop_Invoker&);
263};
264
265template <typename Cvt>
266bool CvtColorIPPLoop(const Mat& src, Mat& dst, const Cvt& cvt)
267{
268 bool ok;
269 parallel_for_(Range(0, src.rows), CvtColorIPPLoop_Invoker<Cvt>(src, dst, cvt, &ok), src.total()/(double)(1<<16) );
270 return ok;
271}
272
273template <typename Cvt>
274bool CvtColorIPPLoopCopy(Mat& src, Mat& dst, const Cvt& cvt)
275{
276 Mat temp;
277 Mat &source = src;
278 if( src.data == dst.data )
279 {
280 src.copyTo(temp);
281 source = temp;
282 }
283 bool ok;
284 parallel_for_(Range(0, source.rows), CvtColorIPPLoop_Invoker<Cvt>(source, dst, cvt, &ok), source.total()/(double)(1<<16) );
285 return ok;
286}

462struct IPPGray2BGRAFunctor
463{
464 IPPGray2BGRAFunctor(ippiGeneralFunc _func1, ippiReorderFunc _func2, int _depth) : func1(_func1), func2(_func2), depth(_depth){}
465 bool operator()(const void *src, int srcStep, void *dst, int dstStep, int cols, int rows) const
466 {
467 const void* srcarray[3] = { src, src, src };
468 Mat temp(rows, cols, CV_MAKETYPE(depth, 3));
469 if(func1(srcarray, srcStep, temp.data, (int)temp.step[0], ippiSize(cols, rows)) < 0)
470 return false;
471 int order[4] = {0, 1, 2, 3};
472 return func2(temp.data, (int)temp.step[0], dst, dstStep, ippiSize(cols, rows), order) >= 0;
473 }
474private:
475 ippiGeneralFunc func1;
476 ippiReorderFunc func2;
477 int depth;
478};

529////////////////// Various 3/4-channel to 3/4-channel RGB transformations /////////////////
530
531template<typename _Tp> struct RGB2RGB
532{
533 typedef _Tp channel_type;
534
535 RGB2RGB(int _srccn, int _dstcn, int _blueIdx) : srccn(_srccn), dstcn(_dstcn), blueIdx(_blueIdx) {}
536 void operator()(const _Tp* src, _Tp* dst, int n) const
537 {
538 int scn = srccn, dcn = dstcn, bidx = blueIdx;
539 if( dcn == 3 )
540 {
541 n *= 3;
542 for( int i = 0; i < n; i += 3, src += scn )
543 {
544 _Tp t0 = src[bidx], t1 = src[1], t2 = src[bidx ^ 2];
545 dst[i] = t0; dst[i+1] = t1; dst[i+2] = t2;
546 }
547 }
548 else if( scn == 3 )
549 {
550 n *= 3;
551 _Tp alpha = ColorChannel<_Tp>::max();
552 for( int i = 0; i < n; i += 3, dst += 4 )
553 {
554 _Tp t0 = src[i], t1 = src[i+1], t2 = src[i+2];
555 dst[bidx] = t0; dst[1] = t1; dst[bidx^2] = t2; dst[3] = alpha;
556 }
557 }
558 else
559 {
560 n *= 4;
561 for( int i = 0; i < n; i += 4 )
562 {
563 _Tp t0 = src[i], t1 = src[i+1], t2 = src[i+2], t3 = src[i+3];
564 dst[i] = t2; dst[i+1] = t1; dst[i+2] = t0; dst[i+3] = t3;
565 }
566 }
567 }
568
569 int srccn, dstcn, blueIdx;
570};

572/////////// Transforming 16-bit (565 or 555) RGB to/from 24/32-bit (888[8]) RGB //////////
573
574struct RGB5x52RGB
575{
576 typedef uchar channel_type;
577
578 RGB5x52RGB(int _dstcn, int _blueIdx, int _greenBits)
579 : dstcn(_dstcn), blueIdx(_blueIdx), greenBits(_greenBits) {}
580
581 void operator()(const uchar* src, uchar* dst, int n) const
582 {
583 int dcn = dstcn, bidx = blueIdx;
584 if( greenBits == 6 )
585 for( int i = 0; i < n; i++, dst += dcn )
586 {
587 unsigned t = ((const ushort*)src)[i];
588 dst[bidx] = (uchar)(t << 3);
589 dst[1] = (uchar)((t >> 3) & ~3);
590 dst[bidx ^ 2] = (uchar)((t >> 8) & ~7);
591 if( dcn == 4 )
592 dst[3] = 255;
593 }
594 else
595 for( int i = 0; i < n; i++, dst += dcn )
596 {
597 unsigned t = ((const ushort*)src)[i];
598 dst[bidx] = (uchar)(t << 3);
599 dst[1] = (uchar)((t >> 2) & ~7);
600 dst[bidx ^ 2] = (uchar)((t >> 7) & ~7);
601 if( dcn == 4 )
602 dst[3] = t & 0x8000 ? 255 : 0;
603 }
604 }
605
606 int dstcn, blueIdx, greenBits;
607};

610struct RGB2RGB5x5
611{
612 typedef uchar channel_type;
613
614 RGB2RGB5x5(int _srccn, int _blueIdx, int _greenBits)
615 : srccn(_srccn), blueIdx(_blueIdx), greenBits(_greenBits) {}
616
617 void operator()(const uchar* src, uchar* dst, int n) const
618 {
619 int scn = srccn, bidx = blueIdx;
620 if( greenBits == 6 )
621 for( int i = 0; i < n; i++, src += scn )
622 {
623 ((ushort*)dst)[i] = (ushort)((src[bidx] >> 3)|((src[1]&~3) << 3)|((src[bidx^2]&~7) << 8));
624 }
625 else if( scn == 3 )
626 for( int i = 0; i < n; i++, src += 3 )
627 {
628 ((ushort*)dst)[i] = (ushort)((src[bidx] >> 3)|((src[1]&~7) << 2)|((src[bidx^2]&~7) << 7));
629 }
630 else
631 for( int i = 0; i < n; i++, src += 4 )
632 {
633 ((ushort*)dst)[i] = (ushort)((src[bidx] >> 3)|((src[1]&~7) << 2)|
634 ((src[bidx^2]&~7) << 7)|(src[3] ? 0x8000 : 0));
635 }
636 }
637
638 int srccn, blueIdx, greenBits;
639};

671struct Gray2RGB5x5
672{
673 typedef uchar channel_type;
674
675 Gray2RGB5x5(int _greenBits) : greenBits(_greenBits) {}
676 void operator()(const uchar* src, uchar* dst, int n) const
677 {
678 if( greenBits == 6 )
679 for( int i = 0; i < n; i++ )
680 {
681 int t = src[i];
682 ((ushort*)dst)[i] = (ushort)((t >> 3)|((t & ~3) << 3)|((t & ~7) << 8));
683 }
684 else
685 for( int i = 0; i < n; i++ )
686 {
687 int t = src[i] >> 3;
688 ((ushort*)dst)[i] = (ushort)(t|(t << 5)|(t << 10));
689 }
690 }

710struct RGB5x52Gray
711{
712 typedef uchar channel_type;
713
714 RGB5x52Gray(int _greenBits) : greenBits(_greenBits) {}
715 void operator()(const uchar* src, uchar* dst, int n) const
716 {
717 if( greenBits == 6 )
718 for( int i = 0; i < n; i++ )
719 {
720 int t = ((ushort*)src)[i];
721 dst[i] = (uchar)CV_DESCALE(((t << 3) & 0xf8)*B2Y +
722 ((t >> 3) & 0xfc)*G2Y +
723 ((t >> 8) & 0xf8)*R2Y, yuv_shift);
724 }
725 else
726 for( int i = 0; i < n; i++ )
727 {
728 int t = ((ushort*)src)[i];
729 dst[i] = (uchar)CV_DESCALE(((t << 3) & 0xf8)*B2Y +
730 ((t >> 2) & 0xf8)*G2Y +
731 ((t >> 7) & 0xf8)*R2Y, yuv_shift);
732 }
733 }

738template<typename _Tp> struct RGB2Gray
739{
740 typedef _Tp channel_type;
741
742 RGB2Gray(int _srccn, int blueIdx, const float* _coeffs) : srccn(_srccn)
743 {
744 static const float coeffs0[] = { R2YF, G2YF, B2YF };
745 memcpy( coeffs, _coeffs ? _coeffs : coeffs0, 3*sizeof(coeffs[0]) );
746 if(blueIdx == 0)
747 std::swap(coeffs[0], coeffs[2]);
748 }
749
750 void operator()(const _Tp* src, _Tp* dst, int n) const
751 {
752 int scn = srccn;
753 float cb = coeffs[0], cg = coeffs[1], cr = coeffs[2];
754 for(int i = 0; i < n; i++, src += scn)
755 dst[i] = saturate_cast<_Tp>(src[0]*cb + src[1]*cg + src[2]*cr);
756 }
757 int srccn;
758 float coeffs[3];
759};

762template<> struct RGB2Gray<uchar>
763{
764 typedef uchar channel_type;
765
766 RGB2Gray(int _srccn, int blueIdx, const int* coeffs) : srccn(_srccn)
767 {
768 const int coeffs0[] = { R2Y, G2Y, B2Y };
769 if(!coeffs) coeffs = coeffs0;
770
771 int b = 0, g = 0, r = (1 << (yuv_shift-1));
772 int db = coeffs[blueIdx^2], dg = coeffs[1], dr = coeffs[blueIdx];
773
774 for( int i = 0; i < 256; i++, b += db, g += dg, r += dr )
775 {
776 tab[i] = b;
777 tab[i+256] = g;
778 tab[i+512] = r;
779 }
780 }
781 void operator()(const uchar* src, uchar* dst, int n) const
782 {
783 int scn = srccn;
784 const int* _tab = tab;
785 for(int i = 0; i < n; i++, src += scn)
786 dst[i] = (uchar)((_tab[src[0]] + _tab[src[1]+256] + _tab[src[2]+512]) >> yuv_shift);
787 }
788 int srccn;
789 int tab[256*3];
790};

818template<typename _Tp> struct RGB2YCrCb_f
819{
820 typedef _Tp channel_type;
821
822 RGB2YCrCb_f(int _srccn, int _blueIdx, bool _isCrCb) : srccn(_srccn), blueIdx(_blueIdx), isCrCb(_isCrCb)
823 {
824 static const float coeffs_crb[] = { R2YF, G2YF, B2YF, YCRF, YCBF };
825 static const float coeffs_yuv[] = { R2YF, G2YF, B2YF, R2VF, B2UF };
826 memcpy(coeffs, isCrCb ? coeffs_crb : coeffs_yuv, 5*sizeof(coeffs[0]));
827 if(blueIdx==0) std::swap(coeffs[0], coeffs[2]);
828 }
829
830 void operator()(const _Tp* src, _Tp* dst, int n) const
831 {
832 int scn = srccn, bidx = blueIdx;
833 int yuvOrder = !isCrCb; //1 if YUV, 0 if YCrCb
834 const _Tp delta = ColorChannel<_Tp>::half();
835 float C0 = coeffs[0], C1 = coeffs[1], C2 = coeffs[2], C3 = coeffs[3], C4 = coeffs[4];
836 n *= 3;
837 for(int i = 0; i < n; i += 3, src += scn)
838 {
839 _Tp Y = saturate_cast<_Tp>(src[0]*C0 + src[1]*C1 + src[2]*C2);
840 _Tp Cr = saturate_cast<_Tp>((src[bidx^2] - Y)*C3 + delta);
841 _Tp Cb = saturate_cast<_Tp>((src[bidx] - Y)*C4 + delta);
842 dst[i] = Y; dst[i+1+yuvOrder] = Cr; dst[i+2-yuvOrder] = Cb;
843 }
844 }
845 int srccn, blueIdx;
846 bool isCrCb;
847 float coeffs[5];
848};

886template<typename _Tp> struct YCrCb2RGB_f
887{
888 typedef _Tp channel_type;
889
890 YCrCb2RGB_f(int _dstcn, int _blueIdx, bool _isCrCb)
891 : dstcn(_dstcn), blueIdx(_blueIdx), isCrCb(_isCrCb)
892 {
893 static const float coeffs_cbr[] = {CR2RF, CR2GF, CB2GF, CB2BF};
894 static const float coeffs_yuv[] = { V2RF, V2GF, U2GF, U2BF};
895 memcpy(coeffs, isCrCb ? coeffs_cbr : coeffs_yuv, 4*sizeof(coeffs[0]));
896 }
897 void operator()(const _Tp* src, _Tp* dst, int n) const
898 {
899 int dcn = dstcn, bidx = blueIdx;
900 int yuvOrder = !isCrCb; //1 if YUV, 0 if YCrCb
901 const _Tp delta = ColorChannel<_Tp>::half(), alpha = ColorChannel<_Tp>::max();
902 float C0 = coeffs[0], C1 = coeffs[1], C2 = coeffs[2], C3 = coeffs[3];
903 n *= 3;
904 for(int i = 0; i < n; i += 3, dst += dcn)
905 {
906 _Tp Y = src[i];
907 _Tp Cr = src[i+1+yuvOrder];
908 _Tp Cb = src[i+2-yuvOrder];
909
910 _Tp b = saturate_cast<_Tp>(Y + (Cb - delta)*C3);
911 _Tp g = saturate_cast<_Tp>(Y + (Cb - delta)*C2 + (Cr - delta)*C1);
912 _Tp r = saturate_cast<_Tp>(Y + (Cr - delta)*C0);
913
914 dst[bidx] = b; dst[1] = g; dst[bidx^2] = r;
915 if( dcn == 4 )
916 dst[3] = alpha;
917 }
918 }
919 int dstcn, blueIdx;
920 bool isCrCb;
921 float coeffs[4];
922};

956 dst[bidx^2] = saturate_cast<_Tp>(r);
957 if( dcn == 4 )
958 dst[3] = alpha;

1149struct RGB2HSV_b
1150{
1151 typedef uchar channel_type;
1152
1153 RGB2HSV_b(int _srccn, int _blueIdx, int _hrange)
1154 : srccn(_srccn), blueIdx(_blueIdx), hrange(_hrange)
1155 {
1156 CV_Assert( hrange == 180 || hrange == 256 );
1157 }
1158
1159 void operator()(const uchar* src, uchar* dst, int n) const
1160 {
1161 int i, bidx = blueIdx, scn = srccn;
1162 const int hsv_shift = 12;
1163
1164 static int sdiv_table[256];
1165 static int hdiv_table180[256];
1166 static int hdiv_table256[256];
1167 static volatile bool initialized = false;
1168
1169 int hr = hrange;
1170 const int* hdiv_table = hr == 180 ? hdiv_table180 : hdiv_table256;
1171 n *= 3;
1172
1173 if( !initialized )
1174 {
1175 sdiv_table[0] = hdiv_table180[0] = hdiv_table256[0] = 0;
1176 for( i = 1; i < 256; i++ )
1177 {
1178 sdiv_table[i] = saturate_cast<int>((255 << hsv_shift)/(1.*i));
1179 hdiv_table180[i] = saturate_cast<int>((180 << hsv_shift)/(6.*i));
1180 hdiv_table256[i] = saturate_cast<int>((256 << hsv_shift)/(6.*i));
1181 }
1182 initialized = true;
1183 }
1184
1185 for( i = 0; i < n; i += 3, src += scn )
1186 {
1187 int b = src[bidx], g = src[1], r = src[bidx^2];
1188 int h, s, v = b;
1189 int vmin = b, diff;
1190 int vr, vg;
1191
1192 CV_CALC_MAX_8U( v, g );
1193 CV_CALC_MAX_8U( v, r );
1194 CV_CALC_MIN_8U( vmin, g );
1195 CV_CALC_MIN_8U( vmin, r );
1196
1197 diff = v - vmin;
1198 vr = v == r ? -1 : 0;
1199 vg = v == g ? -1 : 0;
1200
1201 s = (diff * sdiv_table[v] + (1 << (hsv_shift-1))) >> hsv_shift;
1202 h = (vr & (g - b)) +
1203 (~vr & ((vg & (b - r + 2 * diff)) + ((~vg) & (r - g + 4 * diff))));
1204 h = (h * hdiv_table[diff] + (1 << (hsv_shift-1))) >> hsv_shift;
1205 h += h < 0 ? hr : 0;
1206
1207 dst[i] = saturate_cast<uchar>(h);
1208 dst[i+1] = (uchar)s;
1209 dst[i+2] = (uchar)v;
1210 }
1211 }
1212
1213 int srccn, blueIdx, hrange;
1214};

1571///////////////////////////////////// RGB <-> L*a*b* /////////////////////////////////////
1572
1573static const float D65[] = { 0.950456f, 1.f, 1.088754f };
1574
1575enum { LAB_CBRT_TAB_SIZE = 1024, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE = 1024 };
1576static float LabCbrtTab[LAB_CBRT_TAB_SIZE*4];
1577static const float LabCbrtTabScale = LAB_CBRT_TAB_SIZE/1.5f;
1578
1579static float sRGBGammaTab[GAMMA_TAB_SIZE*4], sRGBInvGammaTab[GAMMA_TAB_SIZE*4];
1580static const float GammaTabScale = (float)GAMMA_TAB_SIZE;
1581
1582static ushort sRGBGammaTab_b[256], linearGammaTab_b[256];
1583#undef lab_shift
1584#define lab_shift xyz_shift
1585#define gamma_shift 3
1586#define lab_shift2 (lab_shift + gamma_shift)
1587#define LAB_CBRT_TAB_SIZE_B (256*3/2*(1<<gamma_shift))
1588static ushort LabCbrtTab_b[LAB_CBRT_TAB_SIZE_B];
1589
1590static void initLabTabs()
1591{
1592 static bool initialized = false;
1593 if(!initialized)
1594 {
1595 float f[LAB_CBRT_TAB_SIZE+1], g[GAMMA_TAB_SIZE+1], ig[GAMMA_TAB_SIZE+1], scale = 1.f/LabCbrtTabScale;
1596 int i;
1597 for(i = 0; i <= LAB_CBRT_TAB_SIZE; i++)
1598 {
1599 float x = i*scale;
1600 f[i] = x < 0.008856f ? x*7.787f + 0.13793103448275862f : cvCbrt(x);
1601 }
1602 splineBuild(f, LAB_CBRT_TAB_SIZE, LabCbrtTab);
1603
1604 scale = 1.f/GammaTabScale;
1605 for(i = 0; i <= GAMMA_TAB_SIZE; i++)
1606 {
1607 float x = i*scale;
1608 g[i] = x <= 0.04045f ? x*(1.f/12.92f) : (float)pow((double)(x + 0.055)*(1./1.055), 2.4);
1609 ig[i] = x <= 0.0031308 ? x*12.92f : (float)(1.055*pow((double)x, 1./2.4) - 0.055);
1610 }
1611 splineBuild(g, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE, sRGBGammaTab);
1612 splineBuild(ig, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE, sRGBInvGammaTab);
1613
1614 for(i = 0; i < 256; i++)
1615 {
1616 float x = i*(1.f/255.f);
1617 sRGBGammaTab_b[i] = saturate_cast<ushort>(255.f*(1 << gamma_shift)*(x <= 0.04045f ? x*(1.f/12.92f) : (float)pow((double)(x + 0.055)*(1./1.055), 2.4)));
1618 linearGammaTab_b[i] = (ushort)(i*(1 << gamma_shift));
1619 }
1620
1621 for(i = 0; i < LAB_CBRT_TAB_SIZE_B; i++)
1622 {
1623 float x = i*(1.f/(255.f*(1 << gamma_shift)));
1624 LabCbrtTab_b[i] = saturate_cast<ushort>((1 << lab_shift2)*(x < 0.008856f ? x*7.787f + 0.13793103448275862f : cvCbrt(x)));
1625 }
1626 initialized = true;
1627 }
1628}

1630struct RGB2Lab_b
1631{
1632 typedef uchar channel_type;
1633
1634 RGB2Lab_b(int _srccn, int blueIdx, const float* _coeffs,
1635 const float* _whitept, bool _srgb)
1636 : srccn(_srccn), srgb(_srgb)
1637 {
1638 static volatile int _3 = 3;
1639 initLabTabs();
1640
1641 if(!_coeffs) _coeffs = sRGB2XYZ_D65;
1642 if(!_whitept) _whitept = D65;
1643 float scale[] =
1644 {
1645 (1 << lab_shift)/_whitept[0],
1646 (float)(1 << lab_shift),
1647 (1 << lab_shift)/_whitept[2]
1648 };
1649
1650 for( int i = 0; i < _3; i++ )
1651 {
1652 coeffs[i*3+(blueIdx^2)] = cvRound(_coeffs[i*3]*scale[i]);
1653 coeffs[i*3+1] = cvRound(_coeffs[i*3+1]*scale[i]);
1654 coeffs[i*3+blueIdx] = cvRound(_coeffs[i*3+2]*scale[i]);
1655
1656 CV_Assert( coeffs[i] >= 0 && coeffs[i*3+1] >= 0 && coeffs[i*3+2] >= 0 &&
1657 coeffs[i*3] + coeffs[i*3+1] + coeffs[i*3+2] < 2*(1 << lab_shift) );
1658 }
1659 }
1660
1661 void operator()(const uchar* src, uchar* dst, int n) const
1662 {
1663 const int Lscale = (116*255+50)/100;
1664 const int Lshift = -((16*255*(1 << lab_shift2) + 50)/100);
1665 const ushort* tab = srgb ? sRGBGammaTab_b : linearGammaTab_b;
1666 int i, scn = srccn;
1667 int C0 = coeffs[0], C1 = coeffs[1], C2 = coeffs[2],
1668 C3 = coeffs[3], C4 = coeffs[4], C5 = coeffs[5],
1669 C6 = coeffs[6], C7 = coeffs[7], C8 = coeffs[8];
1670 n *= 3;
1671
1672 for( i = 0; i < n; i += 3, src += scn )
1673 {
1674 int R = tab[src[0]], G = tab[src[1]], B = tab[src[2]];
1675 int fX = LabCbrtTab_b[CV_DESCALE(R*C0 + G*C1 + B*C2, lab_shift)];
1676 int fY = LabCbrtTab_b[CV_DESCALE(R*C3 + G*C4 + B*C5, lab_shift)];
1677 int fZ = LabCbrtTab_b[CV_DESCALE(R*C6 + G*C7 + B*C8, lab_shift)];
1678
1679 int L = CV_DESCALE( Lscale*fY + Lshift, lab_shift2 );
1680 int a = CV_DESCALE( 500*(fX - fY) + 128*(1 << lab_shift2), lab_shift2 );
1681 int b = CV_DESCALE( 200*(fY - fZ) + 128*(1 << lab_shift2), lab_shift2 );
1682
1683 dst[i] = saturate_cast<uchar>(L);
1684 dst[i+1] = saturate_cast<uchar>(a);
1685 dst[i+2] = saturate_cast<uchar>(b);
1686 }
1687 }
1688
1689 int srccn;
1690 int coeffs[9];
1691 bool srgb;
1692};

1695#define clip(value) \
1696 value < 0.0f ? 0.0f : value > 1.0f ? 1.0f : value;
1697
1698struct RGB2Lab_f
1699{
1700 typedef float channel_type;
1701
1702 RGB2Lab_f(int _srccn, int blueIdx, const float* _coeffs,
1703 const float* _whitept, bool _srgb)
1704 : srccn(_srccn), srgb(_srgb)
1705 {
1706 volatile int _3 = 3;
1707 initLabTabs();
1708
1709 if (!_coeffs)
1710 _coeffs = sRGB2XYZ_D65;
1711 if (!_whitept)
1712 _whitept = D65;
1713
1714 float scale[] = { 1.0f / _whitept[0], 1.0f, 1.0f / _whitept[2] };
1715
1716 for( int i = 0; i < _3; i++ )
1717 {
1718 int j = i * 3;
1719 coeffs[j + (blueIdx ^ 2)] = _coeffs[j] * scale[i];
1720 coeffs[j + 1] = _coeffs[j + 1] * scale[i];
1721 coeffs[j + blueIdx] = _coeffs[j + 2] * scale[i];
1722
1723 CV_Assert( coeffs[j] >= 0 && coeffs[j + 1] >= 0 && coeffs[j + 2] >= 0 &&
1724 coeffs[j] + coeffs[j + 1] + coeffs[j + 2] < 1.5f*LabCbrtTabScale );
1725 }
1726 }
1727
1728 void operator()(const float* src, float* dst, int n) const
1729 {
1730 int i, scn = srccn;
1731 float gscale = GammaTabScale;
1732 const float* gammaTab = srgb ? sRGBGammaTab : 0;
1733 float C0 = coeffs[0], C1 = coeffs[1], C2 = coeffs[2],
1734 C3 = coeffs[3], C4 = coeffs[4], C5 = coeffs[5],
1735 C6 = coeffs[6], C7 = coeffs[7], C8 = coeffs[8];
1736 n *= 3;
1737
1738 static const float _1_3 = 1.0f / 3.0f;
1739 static const float _a = 16.0f / 116.0f;
1740 for (i = 0; i < n; i += 3, src += scn )
1741 {
1742 float R = clip(src[0]);
1743 float G = clip(src[1]);
1744 float B = clip(src[2]);
1745
1746// CV_Assert(R >= 0.0f && R <= 1.0f);
1747// CV_Assert(G >= 0.0f && G <= 1.0f);
1748// CV_Assert(B >= 0.0f && B <= 1.0f);
1749
1750 if (gammaTab)
1751 {
1752 R = splineInterpolate(R * gscale, gammaTab, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE);
1753 G = splineInterpolate(G * gscale, gammaTab, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE);
1754 B = splineInterpolate(B * gscale, gammaTab, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE);
1755 }
1756 float X = R*C0 + G*C1 + B*C2;
1757 float Y = R*C3 + G*C4 + B*C5;
1758 float Z = R*C6 + G*C7 + B*C8;
1759
1760 float FX = X > 0.008856f ? pow(X, _1_3) : (7.787f * X + _a);
1761 float FY = Y > 0.008856f ? pow(Y, _1_3) : (7.787f * Y + _a);
1762 float FZ = Z > 0.008856f ? pow(Z, _1_3) : (7.787f * Z + _a);
1763
1764 float L = Y > 0.008856f ? (116.f * FY - 16.f) : (903.3f * Y);
1765 float a = 500.f * (FX - FY);
1766 float b = 200.f * (FY - FZ);
1767
1768 dst[i] = L;
1769 dst[i + 1] = a;
1770 dst[i + 2] = b;
1771 }
1772 }
1773
1774 int srccn;
1775 float coeffs[9];
1776 bool srgb;
1777};

1779struct Lab2RGB_f
1780{
1781 typedef float channel_type;
1782
1783 Lab2RGB_f( int _dstcn, int blueIdx, const float* _coeffs,
1784 const float* _whitept, bool _srgb )
1785 : dstcn(_dstcn), srgb(_srgb), blueInd(blueIdx)
1786 {
1787 initLabTabs();
1788
1789 if(!_coeffs)
1790 _coeffs = XYZ2sRGB_D65;
1791 if(!_whitept)
1792 _whitept = D65;
1793
1794 for( int i = 0; i < 3; i++ )
1795 {
1796 coeffs[i+(blueIdx^2)*3] = _coeffs[i]*_whitept[i];
1797 coeffs[i+3] = _coeffs[i+3]*_whitept[i];
1798 coeffs[i+blueIdx*3] = _coeffs[i+6]*_whitept[i];
1799 }
1800 }
1801
1802 void operator()(const float* src, float* dst, int n) const
1803 {
1804 int i, dcn = dstcn;
1805 const float* gammaTab = srgb ? sRGBInvGammaTab : 0;
1806 float gscale = GammaTabScale;
1807 float C0 = coeffs[0], C1 = coeffs[1], C2 = coeffs[2],
1808 C3 = coeffs[3], C4 = coeffs[4], C5 = coeffs[5],
1809 C6 = coeffs[6], C7 = coeffs[7], C8 = coeffs[8];
1810 float alpha = ColorChannel<float>::max();
1811 n *= 3;
1812
1813 static const float lThresh = 0.008856f * 903.3f;
1814 static const float fThresh = 7.787f * 0.008856f + 16.0f / 116.0f;
1815 for (i = 0; i < n; i += 3, dst += dcn)
1816 {
1817 float li = src[i];
1818 float ai = src[i + 1];
1819 float bi = src[i + 2];
1820
1821 float y, fy;
1822 if (li <= lThresh)
1823 {
1824 y = li / 903.3f;
1825 fy = 7.787f * y + 16.0f / 116.0f;
1826 }
1827 else
1828 {
1829 fy = (li + 16.0f) / 116.0f;
1830 y = fy * fy * fy;
1831 }
1832
1833 float fxz[] = { ai / 500.0f + fy, fy - bi / 200.0f };
1834
1835 for (int j = 0; j < 2; j++)
1836 if (fxz[j] <= fThresh)
1837 fxz[j] = (fxz[j] - 16.0f / 116.0f) / 7.787f;
1838 else
1839 fxz[j] = fxz[j] * fxz[j] * fxz[j];
1840
1841
1842 float x = fxz[0], z = fxz[1];
1843 float ro = clip(C0 * x + C1 * y + C2 * z);
1844 float go = clip(C3 * x + C4 * y + C5 * z);
1845 float bo = clip(C6 * x + C7 * y + C8 * z);
1846
1847// CV_Assert(ro >= 0.0f && ro <= 1.0f);
1848// CV_Assert(go >= 0.0f && go <= 1.0f);
1849// CV_Assert(bo >= 0.0f && bo <= 1.0f);
1850
1851 if (gammaTab)
1852 {
1853 ro = splineInterpolate(ro * gscale, gammaTab, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE);
1854 go = splineInterpolate(go * gscale, gammaTab, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE);
1855 bo = splineInterpolate(bo * gscale, gammaTab, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE);
1856 }
1857
1858 dst[0] = ro, dst[1] = go, dst[2] = bo;
1859 if( dcn == 4 )
1860 dst[3] = alpha;
1861 }
1862 }
1863
1864 int dstcn;
1865 float coeffs[9];
1866 bool srgb;
1867 int blueInd;
1868};
1869
1870#undef clip

1916struct RGB2Luv_f
1917{
1918 typedef float channel_type;
1919
1920 RGB2Luv_f( int _srccn, int blueIdx, const float* _coeffs,
1921 const float* whitept, bool _srgb )
1922 : srccn(_srccn), srgb(_srgb)
1923 {
1924 volatile int i;
1925 initLabTabs();
1926
1927 if(!_coeffs) _coeffs = sRGB2XYZ_D65;
1928 if(!whitept) whitept = D65;
1929
1930 for( i = 0; i < 3; i++ )
1931 {
1932 coeffs[i*3] = _coeffs[i*3];
1933 coeffs[i*3+1] = _coeffs[i*3+1];
1934 coeffs[i*3+2] = _coeffs[i*3+2];
1935 if( blueIdx == 0 )
1936 std::swap(coeffs[i*3], coeffs[i*3+2]);
1937 CV_Assert( coeffs[i*3] >= 0 && coeffs[i*3+1] >= 0 && coeffs[i*3+2] >= 0 &&
1938 coeffs[i*3] + coeffs[i*3+1] + coeffs[i*3+2] < 1.5f );
1939 }
1940
1941 float d = 1.f/(whitept[0] + whitept[1]*15 + whitept[2]*3);
1942 un = 4*whitept[0]*d;
1943 vn = 9*whitept[1]*d;
1944
1945 CV_Assert(whitept[1] == 1.f);
1946 }
1947
1948 void operator()(const float* src, float* dst, int n) const
1949 {
1950 int i, scn = srccn;
1951 float gscale = GammaTabScale;
1952 const float* gammaTab = srgb ? sRGBGammaTab : 0;
1953 float C0 = coeffs[0], C1 = coeffs[1], C2 = coeffs[2],
1954 C3 = coeffs[3], C4 = coeffs[4], C5 = coeffs[5],
1955 C6 = coeffs[6], C7 = coeffs[7], C8 = coeffs[8];
1956 float _un = 13*un, _vn = 13*vn;
1957 n *= 3;
1958
1959 for( i = 0; i < n; i += 3, src += scn )
1960 {
1961 float R = src[0], G = src[1], B = src[2];
1962 if( gammaTab )
1963 {
1964 R = splineInterpolate(R*gscale, gammaTab, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE);
1965 G = splineInterpolate(G*gscale, gammaTab, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE);
1966 B = splineInterpolate(B*gscale, gammaTab, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE);
1967 }
1968
1969 float X = R*C0 + G*C1 + B*C2;
1970 float Y = R*C3 + G*C4 + B*C5;
1971 float Z = R*C6 + G*C7 + B*C8;
1972
1973 float L = splineInterpolate(Y*LabCbrtTabScale, LabCbrtTab, LAB_CBRT_TAB_SIZE);
1974 L = 116.f*L - 16.f;
1975
1976 float d = (4*13) / std::max(X + 15 * Y + 3 * Z, FLT_EPSILON);
1977 float u = L*(X*d - _un);
1978 float v = L*((9*0.25f)*Y*d - _vn);
1979
1980 dst[i] = L; dst[i+1] = u; dst[i+2] = v;
1981 }
1982 }
1983
1984 int srccn;
1985 float coeffs[9], un, vn;
1986 bool srgb;
1987};

1990struct Luv2RGB_f
1991{
1992 typedef float channel_type;
1993
1994 Luv2RGB_f( int _dstcn, int blueIdx, const float* _coeffs,
1995 const float* whitept, bool _srgb )
1996 : dstcn(_dstcn), srgb(_srgb)
1997 {
1998 initLabTabs();
1999
2000 if(!_coeffs) _coeffs = XYZ2sRGB_D65;
2001 if(!whitept) whitept = D65;
2002
2003 for( int i = 0; i < 3; i++ )
2004 {
2005 coeffs[i+(blueIdx^2)*3] = _coeffs[i];
2006 coeffs[i+3] = _coeffs[i+3];
2007 coeffs[i+blueIdx*3] = _coeffs[i+6];
2008 }
2009
2010 float d = 1.f/(whitept[0] + whitept[1]*15 + whitept[2]*3);
2011 un = 4*whitept[0]*d;
2012 vn = 9*whitept[1]*d;
2013
2014 CV_Assert(whitept[1] == 1.f);
2015 }
2016
2017 void operator()(const float* src, float* dst, int n) const
2018 {
2019 int i, dcn = dstcn;
2020 const float* gammaTab = srgb ? sRGBInvGammaTab : 0;
2021 float gscale = GammaTabScale;
2022 float C0 = coeffs[0], C1 = coeffs[1], C2 = coeffs[2],
2023 C3 = coeffs[3], C4 = coeffs[4], C5 = coeffs[5],
2024 C6 = coeffs[6], C7 = coeffs[7], C8 = coeffs[8];
2025 float alpha = ColorChannel<float>::max();
2026 float _un = un, _vn = vn;
2027 n *= 3;
2028
2029 for( i = 0; i < n; i += 3, dst += dcn )
2030 {
2031 float L = src[i], u = src[i+1], v = src[i+2], d, X, Y, Z;
2032 Y = (L + 16.f) * (1.f/116.f);
2033 Y = Y*Y*Y;
2034 d = (1.f/13.f)/L;
2035 u = u*d + _un;
2036 v = v*d + _vn;
2037 float iv = 1.f/v;
2038 X = 2.25f * u * Y * iv ;
2039 Z = (12 - 3 * u - 20 * v) * Y * 0.25f * iv;
2040
2041 float R = X*C0 + Y*C1 + Z*C2;
2042 float G = X*C3 + Y*C4 + Z*C5;
2043 float B = X*C6 + Y*C7 + Z*C8;
2044
2045 if( gammaTab )
2046 {
2047 R = splineInterpolate(R*gscale, gammaTab, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE);
2048 G = splineInterpolate(G*gscale, gammaTab, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE);
2049 B = splineInterpolate(B*gscale, gammaTab, GAMMA_TAB_SIZE);
2050 }
2051
2052 dst[0] = R; dst[1] = G; dst[2] = B;
2053 if( dcn == 4 )
2054 dst[3] = alpha;
2055 }
2056 }
2057
2058 int dstcn;
2059 float coeffs[9], un, vn;
2060 bool srgb;
2061};

2162#if CV_SSE2
2163class SIMDBayerInterpolator_8u
2164{
2165public:
2166 SIMDBayerInterpolator_8u()
2167 {
2168 use_simd = checkHardwareSupport(CV_CPU_SSE2);
2169 }
2170
2171 int bayer2Gray(const uchar* bayer, int bayer_step, uchar* dst,
2172 int width, int bcoeff, int gcoeff, int rcoeff) const
2173 {
2174 if( !use_simd )
2175 return 0;
2176
2177 __m128i _b2y = _mm_set1_epi16((short)(rcoeff*2));
2178 __m128i _g2y = _mm_set1_epi16((short)(gcoeff*2));
2179 __m128i _r2y = _mm_set1_epi16((short)(bcoeff*2));
2180 const uchar* bayer_end = bayer + width;
2181
2182 for( ; bayer <= bayer_end - 18; bayer += 14, dst += 14 )
2183 {
2184 __m128i r0 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)bayer);
2185 __m128i r1 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(bayer+bayer_step));
2186 __m128i r2 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(bayer+bayer_step*2));
2187
2188 __m128i b1 = _mm_add_epi16(_mm_srli_epi16(_mm_slli_epi16(r0, 8), 7),
2189 _mm_srli_epi16(_mm_slli_epi16(r2, 8), 7));
2190 __m128i b0 = _mm_add_epi16(b1, _mm_srli_si128(b1, 2));
2191 b1 = _mm_slli_epi16(_mm_srli_si128(b1, 2), 1);
2192
2193 __m128i g0 = _mm_add_epi16(_mm_srli_epi16(r0, 7), _mm_srli_epi16(r2, 7));
2194 __m128i g1 = _mm_srli_epi16(_mm_slli_epi16(r1, 8), 7);
2195 g0 = _mm_add_epi16(g0, _mm_add_epi16(g1, _mm_srli_si128(g1, 2)));
2196 g1 = _mm_slli_epi16(_mm_srli_si128(g1, 2), 2);
2197
2198 r0 = _mm_srli_epi16(r1, 8);
2199 r1 = _mm_slli_epi16(_mm_add_epi16(r0, _mm_srli_si128(r0, 2)), 2);
2200 r0 = _mm_slli_epi16(r0, 3);
2201
2202 g0 = _mm_add_epi16(_mm_mulhi_epi16(b0, _b2y), _mm_mulhi_epi16(g0, _g2y));
2203 g1 = _mm_add_epi16(_mm_mulhi_epi16(b1, _b2y), _mm_mulhi_epi16(g1, _g2y));
2204 g0 = _mm_add_epi16(g0, _mm_mulhi_epi16(r0, _r2y));
2205 g1 = _mm_add_epi16(g1, _mm_mulhi_epi16(r1, _r2y));
2206 g0 = _mm_srli_epi16(g0, 2);
2207 g1 = _mm_srli_epi16(g1, 2);
2208 g0 = _mm_packus_epi16(g0, g0);
2209 g1 = _mm_packus_epi16(g1, g1);
2210 g0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(g0, g1);
2211 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)dst, g0);
2212 }
2213
2214 return (int)(bayer - (bayer_end - width));
2215 }
2216
2217 int bayer2RGB(const uchar* bayer, int bayer_step, uchar* dst, int width, int blue) const
2218 {
2219 if( !use_simd )
2220 return 0;
2221 /*
2222 B G B G | B G B G | B G B G | B G B G
2223 G R G R | G R G R | G R G R | G R G R
2224 B G B G | B G B G | B G B G | B G B G
2225 */
2226 __m128i delta1 = _mm_set1_epi16(1), delta2 = _mm_set1_epi16(2);
2227 __m128i mask = _mm_set1_epi16(blue < 0 ? -1 : 0), z = _mm_setzero_si128();
2228 __m128i masklo = _mm_set1_epi16(0x00ff);
2229 const uchar* bayer_end = bayer + width;
2230
2231 for( ; bayer <= bayer_end - 18; bayer += 14, dst += 42 )
2232 {
2233 __m128i r0 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)bayer);
2234 __m128i r1 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(bayer+bayer_step));
2235 __m128i r2 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(bayer+bayer_step*2));
2236
2237 __m128i b1 = _mm_add_epi16(_mm_and_si128(r0, masklo), _mm_and_si128(r2, masklo));
2238 __m128i b0 = _mm_add_epi16(b1, _mm_srli_si128(b1, 2));
2239 b1 = _mm_srli_si128(b1, 2);
2240 b1 = _mm_srli_epi16(_mm_add_epi16(b1, delta1), 1);
2241 b0 = _mm_srli_epi16(_mm_add_epi16(b0, delta2), 2);
2242 b0 = _mm_packus_epi16(b0, b1);
2243
2244 __m128i g0 = _mm_add_epi16(_mm_srli_epi16(r0, 8), _mm_srli_epi16(r2, 8));
2245 __m128i g1 = _mm_and_si128(r1, masklo);
2246 g0 = _mm_add_epi16(g0, _mm_add_epi16(g1, _mm_srli_si128(g1, 2)));
2247 g1 = _mm_srli_si128(g1, 2);
2248 g0 = _mm_srli_epi16(_mm_add_epi16(g0, delta2), 2);
2249 g0 = _mm_packus_epi16(g0, g1);
2250
2251 r0 = _mm_srli_epi16(r1, 8);
2252 r1 = _mm_add_epi16(r0, _mm_srli_si128(r0, 2));
2253 r1 = _mm_srli_epi16(_mm_add_epi16(r1, delta1), 1);
2254 r0 = _mm_packus_epi16(r0, r1);
2255
2256 b1 = _mm_and_si128(_mm_xor_si128(b0, r0), mask);
2257 b0 = _mm_xor_si128(b0, b1);
2258 r0 = _mm_xor_si128(r0, b1);
2259
2260 // b1 g1 b1 g1 ...
2261 b1 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(b0, g0);
2262 // b0 g0 b2 g2 b4 g4 ....
2263 b0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(b0, g0);
2264
2265 // r1 0 r3 0 ...
2266 r1 = _mm_unpackhi_epi8(r0, z);
2267 // r0 0 r2 0 r4 0 ...
2268 r0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(r0, z);
2269
2270 // 0 b0 g0 r0 0 b2 g2 r2 0 ...
2271 g0 = _mm_slli_si128(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(b0, r0), 1);
2272 // 0 b8 g8 r8 0 b10 g10 r10 0 ...
2273 g1 = _mm_slli_si128(_mm_unpackhi_epi16(b0, r0), 1);
2274
2275 // b1 g1 r1 0 b3 g3 r3 ....
2276 r0 = _mm_unpacklo_epi16(b1, r1);
2277 // b9 g9 r9 0 ...
2278 r1 = _mm_unpackhi_epi16(b1, r1);
2279
2280 b0 = _mm_srli_si128(_mm_unpacklo_epi32(g0, r0), 1);
2281 b1 = _mm_srli_si128(_mm_unpackhi_epi32(g0, r0), 1);
2282
2283 _mm_storel_epi64((__m128i*)(dst-1+0), b0);
2284 _mm_storel_epi64((__m128i*)(dst-1+6*1), _mm_srli_si128(b0, 8));
2285 _mm_storel_epi64((__m128i*)(dst-1+6*2), b1);
2286 _mm_storel_epi64((__m128i*)(dst-1+6*3), _mm_srli_si128(b1, 8));
2287
2288 g0 = _mm_srli_si128(_mm_unpacklo_epi32(g1, r1), 1);
2289 g1 = _mm_srli_si128(_mm_unpackhi_epi32(g1, r1), 1);
2290
2291 _mm_storel_epi64((__m128i*)(dst-1+6*4), g0);
2292 _mm_storel_epi64((__m128i*)(dst-1+6*5), _mm_srli_si128(g0, 8));
2293
2294 _mm_storel_epi64((__m128i*)(dst-1+6*6), g1);
2295 }
2296
2297 return (int)(bayer - (bayer_end - width));
2298 }
2299
2300 bool use_simd;
2301};
2302#else

2306template<typename T, class SIMDInterpolator>
2307static void Bayer2Gray_( const Mat& srcmat, Mat& dstmat, int code )
2308{
2309 SIMDInterpolator vecOp;
2310 const int R2Y = 4899;
2311 const int G2Y = 9617;
2312 const int B2Y = 1868;
2313 const int SHIFT = 14;
2314
2315 const T* bayer0 = (const T*)srcmat.data;
2316 int bayer_step = (int)(srcmat.step/sizeof(T));
2317 T* dst0 = (T*)dstmat.data;
2318 int dst_step = (int)(dstmat.step/sizeof(T));
2319 Size size = srcmat.size();
2320 int bcoeff = B2Y, rcoeff = R2Y;
2321 int start_with_green = code == CV_BayerGB2GRAY || code == CV_BayerGR2GRAY;
2322 bool brow = true;
2323
2324 if( code != CV_BayerBG2GRAY && code != CV_BayerGB2GRAY )
2325 {
2326 brow = false;
2327 std::swap(bcoeff, rcoeff);
2328 }
2329
2330 dst0 += dst_step + 1;
2331 size.height -= 2;
2332 size.width -= 2;
2333
2334 for( ; size.height-- > 0; bayer0 += bayer_step, dst0 += dst_step )
2335 {
2336 unsigned t0, t1, t2;
2337 const T* bayer = bayer0;
2338 T* dst = dst0;
2339 const T* bayer_end = bayer + size.width;
2340
2341 if( size.width <= 0 )
2342 {
2343 dst[-1] = dst[size.width] = 0;
2344 continue;
2345 }
2346
2347 if( start_with_green )
2348 {
2349 t0 = (bayer[1] + bayer[bayer_step*2+1])*rcoeff;
2350 t1 = (bayer[bayer_step] + bayer[bayer_step+2])*bcoeff;
2351 t2 = bayer[bayer_step+1]*(2*G2Y);
2352
2353 dst[0] = (T)CV_DESCALE(t0 + t1 + t2, SHIFT+1);
2354 bayer++;
2355 dst++;
2356 }
2357
2358 int delta = vecOp.bayer2Gray(bayer, bayer_step, dst, size.width, bcoeff, G2Y, rcoeff);
2359 bayer += delta;
2360 dst += delta;
2361
2362 for( ; bayer <= bayer_end - 2; bayer += 2, dst += 2 )
2363 {
2364 t0 = (bayer[0] + bayer[2] + bayer[bayer_step*2] + bayer[bayer_step*2+2])*rcoeff;
2365 t1 = (bayer[1] + bayer[bayer_step] + bayer[bayer_step+2] + bayer[bayer_step*2+1])*G2Y;
2366 t2 = bayer[bayer_step+1]*(4*bcoeff);
2367 dst[0] = (T)CV_DESCALE(t0 + t1 + t2, SHIFT+2);
2368
2369 t0 = (bayer[2] + bayer[bayer_step*2+2])*rcoeff;
2370 t1 = (bayer[bayer_step+1] + bayer[bayer_step+3])*bcoeff;
2371 t2 = bayer[bayer_step+2]*(2*G2Y);
2372 dst[1] = (T)CV_DESCALE(t0 + t1 + t2, SHIFT+1);
2373 }
2374
2375 if( bayer < bayer_end )
2376 {
2377 t0 = (bayer[0] + bayer[2] + bayer[bayer_step*2] + bayer[bayer_step*2+2])*rcoeff;
2378 t1 = (bayer[1] + bayer[bayer_step] + bayer[bayer_step+2] + bayer[bayer_step*2+1])*G2Y;
2379 t2 = bayer[bayer_step+1]*(4*bcoeff);
2380 dst[0] = (T)CV_DESCALE(t0 + t1 + t2, SHIFT+2);
2381 bayer++;
2382 dst++;
2383 }
2384
2385 dst0[-1] = dst0[0];
2386 dst0[size.width] = dst0[size.width-1];
2387
2388 brow = !brow;
2389 std::swap(bcoeff, rcoeff);
2390 start_with_green = !start_with_green;
2391 }
2392
2393 size = dstmat.size();
2394 dst0 = (T*)dstmat.data;
2395 if( size.height > 2 )
2396 for( int i = 0; i < size.width; i++ )
2397 {
2398 dst0[i] = dst0[i + dst_step];
2399 dst0[i + (size.height-1)*dst_step] = dst0[i + (size.height-2)*dst_step];
2400 }
2401 else
2402 for( int i = 0; i < size.width; i++ )
2403 {
2404 dst0[i] = dst0[i + (size.height-1)*dst_step] = 0;
2405 }
2406}

2477 bayer[bayer_step*2+2] + 2) >> 2;
2478 t1 = (bayer[1] + bayer[bayer_step] +
2479 bayer[bayer_step+2] + bayer[bayer_step*2+1]+2) >> 2;
2480 dst[1] = (T)t0;
2481 dst[0] = (T)t1;
2482 dst[-1] = bayer[bayer_step+1];
2483
2484 t0 = (bayer[2] + bayer[bayer_step*2+2] + 1) >> 1;
2485 t1 = (bayer[bayer_step+1] + bayer[bayer_step+3] + 1) >> 1;

2507 dst0[-2] = dst0[1];
2508 dst0[size.width*3-1] = dst0[size.width*3-4];
2509 dst0[size.width*3] = dst0[size.width*3-3];
2510 dst0[size.width*3+1] = dst0[size.width*3-2];

2520 {

2523 }
2524 else
2525 for( int i = 0; i < size.width*3; i++ )
2526 {
2527 dst0[i] = dst0[i + (size.height-1)*dst_step] = 0;

2792 if( gradSW < T )
2793 {
2794 Rs += srow[bstep*2-1] + srow[-1];
2795 Gs += srow[bstep-1]*2;
2796 Bs += srow[bstep] + srow[bstep-2];
2797 ng++;
2798 }
2799 if( gradNW < T )
2800 {
2801 Rs += srow[-bstep*2-1] + srow[-1];
2802 Gs += srow[-bstep-1]*2;
2803 Bs += srow[-bstep-2]+srow[-bstep];
2804 ng++;
2805 }
2806 if( gradSE < T )
2807 {
2808 Rs += srow[bstep*2+1] + srow[1];
2809 Gs += srow[bstep+1]*2;
2810 Bs += srow[bstep+2]+srow[bstep];
2811 ng++;
2812 }
2813 G = srow[0];
2814 R = G + cvRound((Rs - Gs)*scale[ng]);
2815 B = G + cvRound((Bs - Gs)*scale[ng]);
2816 }
2817 dstrow[blueIdx] = CV_CAST_8U(B);
2818 dstrow[1] = CV_CAST_8U(G);
2819 dstrow[blueIdx^2] = CV_CAST_8U(R);
2820 greenCell = !greenCell;
2821 }

2823#if CV_SSE2

2825 break;

2827 __m128i emask = _mm_set1_epi32(0x0000ffff),
2828 omask = _mm_set1_epi32(0xffff0000),
2829 z = _mm_setzero_si128(),
2830 one = _mm_set1_epi16(1);
2831 __m128 _0_5 = _mm_set1_ps(0.5f);

2833 #define _mm_merge_epi16(a, b) _mm_or_si128(_mm_and_si128(a, emask), _mm_and_si128(b, omask)) //(aA_aA_aA_aA) * (bB_bB_bB_bB) => (bA_bA_bA_bA)
2834 #define _mm_cvtloepi16_ps(a) _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(a,a), 16)) //(1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8) => (1f,2f,3f,4f)
2835 #define _mm_cvthiepi16_ps(a) _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_srai_epi32(_mm_unpackhi_epi16(a,a), 16)) //(1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8) => (5f,6f,7f,8f)

3000 // Bs += {srow[bstep-1]*2; (srow[bstep]+srow[bstep-2])} * (T>gradSW)

3053 _mm_storel_epi64(blueIdx ? (__m128i*)R : (__m128i*)B, _mm_packus_epi16(t1, z));
3054
3055 for( int j = 0; j < 8; j++, dstrow += 3 )
3056 {
3057 dstrow[0] = B[j]; dstrow[1] = G[j]; dstrow[2] = R[j];
3058 }
3059 }
3060#endif
3061
3062 limit = N - 2;
3063 }
3064 while( i < N - 2 );
3065
3066 for( i = 0; i < 6; i++ )
3067 {
3068 dst[dststep*y + 5 - i] = dst[dststep*y + 8 - i];
3069 dst[dststep*y + (N - 2)*3 + i] = dst[dststep*y + (N - 3)*3 + i];
3070 }
3071
3072 greenCell0 = !greenCell0;
3073 blueIdx ^= 2;
3074 }
3075
3076 for( i = 0; i < size.width*3; i++ )
3077 {
3078 dst[i] = dst[i + dststep] = dst[i + dststep*2];
3079 dst[i + dststep*(size.height-4)] =
3080 dst[i + dststep*(size.height-3)] =
3081 dst[i + dststep*(size.height-2)] =
3082 dst[i + dststep*(size.height-1)] = dst[i + dststep*(size.height-5)];
3083 }
3084}

3112 YUV420sp2RGB888Invoker(Mat* _dst, int _stride, const uchar* _y1, const uchar* _uv)

3429///////////////////////////////////// RGB -> YUV420p /////////////////////////////////////
3430
3431template<int bIdx>
3432struct RGB888toYUV420pInvoker: public ParallelLoopBody
3433{
3434 RGB888toYUV420pInvoker( const Mat& src, Mat* dst, const int uIdx )
3435 : src_(src),
3436 dst_(dst),
3437 uIdx_(uIdx) { }
3438
3439 void operator()(const Range& rowRange) const
3440 {
3441 const int w = src_.cols;
3442 const int h = src_.rows;
3443
3444 const int cn = src_.channels();
3445 for( int i = rowRange.start; i < rowRange.end; i++ )
3446 {
3447 const uchar* row0 = src_.ptr<uchar>(2 * i);
3448 const uchar* row1 = src_.ptr<uchar>(2 * i + 1);
3449
3450 uchar* y = dst_->ptr<uchar>(2*i);
3451 uchar* u = dst_->ptr<uchar>(h + i/2) + (i % 2) * (w/2);
3452 uchar* v = dst_->ptr<uchar>(h + (i + h/2)/2) + ((i + h/2) % 2) * (w/2);
3453 if( uIdx_ == 2 ) std::swap(u, v);
3454
3455 for( int j = 0, k = 0; j < w * cn; j += 2 * cn, k++ )
3456 {
3457 int r00 = row0[2-bIdx + j]; int g00 = row0[1 + j]; int b00 = row0[bIdx + j];
3458 int r01 = row0[2-bIdx + cn + j]; int g01 = row0[1 + cn + j]; int b01 = row0[bIdx + cn + j];
3459 int r10 = row1[2-bIdx + j]; int g10 = row1[1 + j]; int b10 = row1[bIdx + j];
3460 int r11 = row1[2-bIdx + cn + j]; int g11 = row1[1 + cn + j]; int b11 = row1[bIdx + cn + j];
3461
3462 const int shifted16 = (16 << ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3463 const int halfShift = (1 << (ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT - 1));
3464 int y00 = ITUR_BT_601_CRY * r00 + ITUR_BT_601_CGY * g00 + ITUR_BT_601_CBY * b00 + halfShift + shifted16;
3465 int y01 = ITUR_BT_601_CRY * r01 + ITUR_BT_601_CGY * g01 + ITUR_BT_601_CBY * b01 + halfShift + shifted16;
3466 int y10 = ITUR_BT_601_CRY * r10 + ITUR_BT_601_CGY * g10 + ITUR_BT_601_CBY * b10 + halfShift + shifted16;
3467 int y11 = ITUR_BT_601_CRY * r11 + ITUR_BT_601_CGY * g11 + ITUR_BT_601_CBY * b11 + halfShift + shifted16;
3468
3469 y[2*k + 0] = saturate_cast<uchar>(y00 >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3470 y[2*k + 1] = saturate_cast<uchar>(y01 >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3471 y[2*k + dst_->step + 0] = saturate_cast<uchar>(y10 >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3472 y[2*k + dst_->step + 1] = saturate_cast<uchar>(y11 >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3473
3474 const int shifted128 = (128 << ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3475 int u00 = ITUR_BT_601_CRU * r00 + ITUR_BT_601_CGU * g00 + ITUR_BT_601_CBU * b00 + halfShift + shifted128;
3476 int v00 = ITUR_BT_601_CBU * r00 + ITUR_BT_601_CGV * g00 + ITUR_BT_601_CBV * b00 + halfShift + shifted128;
3477
3478 u[k] = saturate_cast<uchar>(u00 >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3479 v[k] = saturate_cast<uchar>(v00 >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3480 }
3481 }
3482 }
3483
3484 static bool isFit( const Mat& src )
3485 {
3486 return (src.total() >= 320*240);
3487 }
3488
3489private:
3490 RGB888toYUV420pInvoker& operator=(const RGB888toYUV420pInvoker&);
3491
3492 const Mat& src_;
3493 Mat* const dst_;
3494 const int uIdx_;
3495};

3498static void cvtRGBtoYUV420p(const Mat& src, Mat& dst)
3499{
3500 RGB888toYUV420pInvoker<bIdx> colorConverter(src, &dst, uIdx);
3501 if( RGB888toYUV420pInvoker<bIdx>::isFit(src) )
3502 parallel_for_(Range(0, src.rows/2), colorConverter);
3503 else
3504 colorConverter(Range(0, src.rows/2));
3505}

3520 {
3521 int rangeBegin = range.start;
3522 int rangeEnd = range.end;
3523

3528 for (int j = rangeBegin; j < rangeEnd; j++, yuv_src += stride)
3529 {
3530 uchar* row = dst->ptr<uchar>(j);
3531
3532 for (int i = 0; i < 2 * width; i += 4, row += 6)
3533 {
3534 int u = int(yuv_src[i + uidx]) - 128;
3535 int v = int(yuv_src[i + vidx]) - 128;
3536
3537 int ruv = (1 << (ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT - 1)) + ITUR_BT_601_CVR * v;
3538 int guv = (1 << (ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT - 1)) + ITUR_BT_601_CVG * v + ITUR_BT_601_CUG * u;
3539 int buv = (1 << (ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT - 1)) + ITUR_BT_601_CUB * u;
3540
3541 int y00 = std::max(0, int(yuv_src[i + yIdx]) - 16) * ITUR_BT_601_CY;
3542 row[2-bIdx] = saturate_cast<uchar>((y00 + ruv) >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3543 row[1] = saturate_cast<uchar>((y00 + guv) >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3544 row[bIdx] = saturate_cast<uchar>((y00 + buv) >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3545
3546 int y01 = std::max(0, int(yuv_src[i + yIdx + 2]) - 16) * ITUR_BT_601_CY;
3547 row[5-bIdx] = saturate_cast<uchar>((y01 + ruv) >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3548 row[4] = saturate_cast<uchar>((y01 + guv) >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3549 row[3+bIdx] = saturate_cast<uchar>((y01 + buv) >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3550 }
3551 }
3552 }
3553};
3554
3555template<int bIdx, int uIdx, int yIdx>
3556struct YUV422toRGBA8888Invoker : ParallelLoopBody
3557{
3558 Mat* dst;
3559 const uchar* src;
3560 int width, stride;
3561
3562 YUV422toRGBA8888Invoker(Mat* _dst, int _stride, const uchar* _yuv)
3563 : dst(_dst), src(_yuv), width(_dst->cols), stride(_stride) {}
3564
3565 void operator()(const Range& range) const
3566 {
3567 int rangeBegin = range.start;
3568 int rangeEnd = range.end;
3569
3570 const int uidx = 1 - yIdx + uIdx * 2;
3571 const int vidx = (2 + uidx) % 4;
3572 const uchar* yuv_src = src + rangeBegin * stride;
3573
3574 for (int j = rangeBegin; j < rangeEnd; j++, yuv_src += stride)
3575 {
3576 uchar* row = dst->ptr<uchar>(j);
3577
3578 for (int i = 0; i < 2 * width; i += 4, row += 8)
3579 {
3580 int u = int(yuv_src[i + uidx]) - 128;
3581 int v = int(yuv_src[i + vidx]) - 128;
3582
3583 int ruv = (1 << (ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT - 1)) + ITUR_BT_601_CVR * v;
3584 int guv = (1 << (ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT - 1)) + ITUR_BT_601_CVG * v + ITUR_BT_601_CUG * u;
3585 int buv = (1 << (ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT - 1)) + ITUR_BT_601_CUB * u;
3586
3587 int y00 = std::max(0, int(yuv_src[i + yIdx]) - 16) * ITUR_BT_601_CY;
3588 row[2-bIdx] = saturate_cast<uchar>((y00 + ruv) >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3589 row[1] = saturate_cast<uchar>((y00 + guv) >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3590 row[bIdx] = saturate_cast<uchar>((y00 + buv) >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3591 row[3] = uchar(0xff);
3592
3593 int y01 = std::max(0, int(yuv_src[i + yIdx + 2]) - 16) * ITUR_BT_601_CY;
3594 row[6-bIdx] = saturate_cast<uchar>((y01 + ruv) >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3595 row[5] = saturate_cast<uchar>((y01 + guv) >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3596 row[4+bIdx] = saturate_cast<uchar>((y01 + buv) >> ITUR_BT_601_SHIFT);
3597 row[7] = uchar(0xff);
3598 }
3599 }
3600 }
3601};
3602
3603#define MIN_SIZE_FOR_PARALLEL_YUV422_CONVERSION (320*240)
3604
3605template<int bIdx, int uIdx, int yIdx>
3606inline void cvtYUV422toRGB(Mat& _dst, int _stride, const uchar* _yuv)
3607{
3608 YUV422toRGB888Invoker<bIdx, uIdx, yIdx> converter(&_dst, _stride, _yuv);
3609 if (_dst.total() >= MIN_SIZE_FOR_PARALLEL_YUV422_CONVERSION)
3610 parallel_for_(Range(0, _dst.rows), converter);
3611 else
3612 converter(Range(0, _dst.rows));
3613}
3614
3615template<int bIdx, int uIdx, int yIdx>
3616inline void cvtYUV422toRGBA(Mat& _dst, int _stride, const uchar* _yuv)
3617{
3618 YUV422toRGBA8888Invoker<bIdx, uIdx, yIdx> converter(&_dst, _stride, _yuv);
3619 if (_dst.total() >= MIN_SIZE_FOR_PARALLEL_YUV422_CONVERSION)
3620 parallel_for_(Range(0, _dst.rows), converter);
3621 else
3622 converter(Range(0, _dst.rows));
3623}

3625/////////////////////////// RGBA <-> mRGBA (alpha premultiplied) //////////////
3626
3627template<typename _Tp>
3628struct RGBA2mRGBA
3629{
3630 typedef _Tp channel_type;
3631
3632 void operator()(const _Tp* src, _Tp* dst, int n) const
3633 {
3634 _Tp max_val = ColorChannel<_Tp>::max();
3635 _Tp half_val = ColorChannel<_Tp>::half();
3636 for( int i = 0; i < n; i++ )
3637 {
3638 _Tp v0 = *src++;
3639 _Tp v1 = *src++;
3640 _Tp v2 = *src++;
3641 _Tp v3 = *src++;
3642
3643 *dst++ = (v0 * v3 + half_val) / max_val;
3644 *dst++ = (v1 * v3 + half_val) / max_val;
3645 *dst++ = (v2 * v3 + half_val) / max_val;
3646 *dst++ = v3;
3647 }
3648 }
3649};
3650
3651
3652template<typename _Tp>
3653struct mRGBA2RGBA
3654{
3655 typedef _Tp channel_type;
3656
3657 void operator()(const _Tp* src, _Tp* dst, int n) const
3658 {
3659 _Tp max_val = ColorChannel<_Tp>::max();
3660 for( int i = 0; i < n; i++ )
3661 {
3662 _Tp v0 = *src++;
3663 _Tp v1 = *src++;
3664 _Tp v2 = *src++;
3665 _Tp v3 = *src++;
3666 _Tp v3_half = v3 / 2;
3667
3668 *dst++ = (v3==0)? 0 : (v0 * max_val + v3_half) / v3;
3669 *dst++ = (v3==0)? 0 : (v1 * max_val + v3_half) / v3;
3670 *dst++ = (v3==0)? 0 : (v2 * max_val + v3_half) / v3;
3671 *dst++ = v3;
3672 }
3673 }
3674};

4428 CvtColorLoop(src, dst, RGBA2mRGBA<uchar>());
4429 } else {
4430 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Unsupported image depth" );
4431 }
4432 }
4433 break;
4434 case CV_mRGBA2RGBA:
4435 {
4436 if (dcn <= 0) dcn = 4;
4437 CV_Assert( scn == 4 && dcn == 4 );
4438
4439 _dst.create(sz, CV_MAKETYPE(depth, dcn));
4440 dst = _dst.getMat();
4441
4442 if( depth == CV_8U )
4443 {
4444 CvtColorLoop(src, dst, mRGBA2RGBA<uchar>());
4445 } else {
4446 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Unsupported image depth" );
4447 }
4448 }
4449 break;
4450 default:
4451 CV_Error( CV_StsBadFlag, "Unknown/unsupported color conversion code" );
4452 }
4453}

4455CV_IMPL void
4456cvCvtColor( const CvArr* srcarr, CvArr* dstarr, int code )
4457{
4458 cv::Mat src = cv::cvarrToMat(srcarr), dst0 = cv::cvarrToMat(dstarr), dst = dst0;
4459 CV_Assert( src.depth() == dst.depth() );
4460
4461 cv::cvtColor(src, dst, code, dst.channels());
4462 CV_Assert( dst.data == dst0.data );
4463}
